We see that from Monday to Thursday the peak demand from our simulation corresponds quite well with the real peak demand. However, for Fridays it is not so good, so maybe it would be convenient to consider Fridays as a separate time-cycle instead of considering it a normal working day. The demand on weekends is also not really accurate due to the low amount of sessions. Obviously, the stochastic simulations work better with large amounts of data since the aggregation makes the random component not so relevant.
